  "heritageSetupTitle": "Set up an heir",
  "heritageSetupBody": "A password distinct from yours will let a relative (spouse, child, executor) access the vault contents **after a long period of inactivity** on your part (90 days by default + 7 days of grace).\n\nKeep in mind:\n• The heir password must differ from your main password\n• Share it with your heir securely (verbally, will, bank vault) — it is never stored and cannot be recovered\n• The heir gets a snapshot of the vault. Remember to update it regularly.\n• If you log back in before the grace ends, the countdown is reset.\n• The existence of an heritage snapshot is detectable by forensic analysis of the phone (no plausible deniability — for that, see the decoy vault).\n\nThis system runs 100% locally, with no cloud or third party.",
